BugME
AI Study Buddy 🤖📚
Project Description
AI Study Buddy is an intelligent academic companion designed to enhance your study experience. Developed with a focus on personalized learning, this application uses a powerful combination of artificial intelligence and modern web technologies to help students manage their coursework, prepare for exams, and study more effectively. By leveraging cutting-edge OCR models for document analysis, AI Study Buddy provides a seamless, all-in-one platform for your educational needs.

Features
Syllabus & Document Upload: Upload your syllabus and other study materials to the platform, which uses advanced OCR models to parse content.

Exam Preparation: Track upcoming exams and create a personalized study plan to prepare efficiently.

Study Notes: Create, organize, and manage your study notes directly within the application.

Quiz Generation: Automatically generate quizzes from your uploaded materials to test your knowledge.

Interactive AI Chatbot: Talk to an AI chatbot to ask questions and get help with your studies in real-time.

Calendar Notifications: Receive timely notifications and reminders from a connected calendar to stay on top of your schedule.

Technologies Used
The AI Study Buddy is built with a powerful and flexible technology stack to ensure a responsive and intelligent user experience.

Frontend:

React: A popular JavaScript library for building the user interface.

Tailwind CSS: A utility-first CSS framework for fast and custom styling.

JavaScript: The core programming language for the frontend logic.

Backend & AI:

Python: The main language for backend logic and AI model integration.

OCR Models: Optical Character Recognition models, used for analyzing and extracting text from uploaded documents like syllabi.

Firebase: A backend-as-a-service platform for user authentication, real-time database, and cloud functions.

Version Control:

Git & GitHub: For collaborative development and code management.

Getting Started
To get a local copy up and running, follow these steps.

Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed:

Node.js (LTS version recommended)

npm or Yarn

Python

Installation
Clone the repository:

Bash

git clone https://github.com/keshavgarg616/BugME
Navigate to the project directory:

Bash

cd AI-Study-Buddy
Install dependencies for both frontend and backend:

Bash

# Install Python dependencies (backend)
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Navigate to the client directory and install frontend dependencies
cd client
npm install
Run the application:

Bash

# Start the backend server
python app.py

# Start the frontend development server
npm start
The application will be accessible at http://localhost:3000.

